This paper deals with language modeling and domain adaptation for reading comprehension, which are topics that are commonly studied in the natural language processing (NLP) community. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes two models that use multi-task learning and sequential learning, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) research. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of unsupervised learning, which is a common technique in neural networks (NN) and reinforcement learning (RL) research. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of textual sources and biomedical domains, which are topics commonly studied in computer vision (CV) and bioinformatics research. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
